  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Given an array of both the positive integers ans the negative integers, write a program to count the pair for the given difference\n\n\n\nNote : Pair should be counted only once\n\n\n\nFor Example:\n\nThe input array is :{3,34,-5,12,78,14,8,17,58}\n\nThe given sum is : 20\n\nThe output is : 2\n\nExplanation:\n\nwhen we subtract 34 & 14 we will get 20\n\n78-58=20\n\n\n\nHence the pair count is 2.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N <= 10^5",
      "1 <= arr[i] <= 10^9"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains the size of the array.\n\nSecond line contains the array elements.\n\nThird line contains the difference.",
    "outputFormat": "Print the count.",
